abstract: Turkish politician Mehmet Ali Ediboglu tells British newspaper The Observer that he believes six medical students and three recent graduates, all Britons, have secretly traveled to Syria to work in region under Islamic State control.
lead_paragraph: A Turkish politician who met with the families told The Observer that he believed the six students and three recent graduates were in a Syrian town under ISIS control.

headline.main: Medical Students From Britain Are Sought in Syria
headline.print_headline: Students From Britain Are Sought in Syria
